  "title": "RESIDENT TECHNICAL OFFICER",
  "description": "<p>Job Responsibilities:</p>\n<p>Co-ordinate and liaise between the Board and the Project Contractor.<br>\nArrange and supervise Site Acceptance Test and Factory Acceptance Test as may be necessary, including the review of samples submitted by Project Contractor<br>\nCheck on the quality of materials delivered to site and report to the Board any material that does not conform to the specifications.<br>\nCheck the Project Contractor’s claims and advise the Board on appropriate actions to be taken.<br>\nAssist the Board to verify all variation works carried out on site.<br>\nEnsure the safety, cleanliness, tidiness, and Earth Control Measure (ECM) are provided and maintained on site, if and when required.<br>\nRTO shall include daily monitoring of site works and update of daily activities done by Project Contractor as part of his job scope.<br>\nRTO shall also assist in verifying transmittals, method statements, risk assessment and submission submitted by Project Contractor to ensure compliance to Specifications.<br>\nRTO shall also assist to certify work done each month for Contract payment purposes to be processed by the Board.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Minimally a Diploma qualified</li>\n  <li>The candidate must be a registered Resident Technical Officer with BCA.</li>\n  <li>At least two (3) years site supervisory experience in M&amp;E projects</li>\n  <li>Must be literate in English and have adequate knowledge to use computer, reply to emails, use computer software, e.g. Microsoft Word, Excel etc.</li>\n</ul>",
